{"type":"session_message","session_id":"ses_289464e49ffe0PfCgeymUZjBBs","role":"assistant","message_id":"msg_d76ba0452001pxQM9I0nCrDH05","parts":[{"id":"prt_d76ba11d400162LmDKpHNuLjOI","messageID":"msg_d76ba0452001pxQM9I0nCrDH05","sessionID":"ses_289464e49ffe0PfCgeymUZjBBs","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_84a167136a8d400193be30c0","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/workspace/docs/source/index.rst"},"output":"<path>/workspace/docs/source/index.rst</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>1: .. .. seealso::\n2: ..   * :ref:`Installing <installing>`\n3: ..   * :ref:`About Ajenti <man-about>`\n4: ..   * :ref:`Plugin development <dev-getting-started>`\n5: ..   * :ref:`Core development <dev-getting-started-core>`\n6: \n7: Ajenti Web Interface Platform\n8: -----------------------------\n9: \n10: Ajenti platform includes following products:\n11: \n12: * **Ajenti Core**, a Python library, the platform itself including the HTTP server, socket engine and plugin container.\n13: * **Ajenti Panel**, a startup script and a set of stock plugins such as file manager, network configurator and service manager.\n14: \n15: Feature Overview\n16: ----------------\n17: \n18: HTTP Server\n19: ===========\n20: \n21: * HTTP 1.1 Support.\n22: * Websockets with fallback to XHR polling.\n23: * Fast event-loop based processing.\n24: * Flexible routing.\n25: * Session sandboxing.\n26: * SSL with client certificate authentication.\n27: \n28: Performance\n29: ===========\n30: \n31: * >1000 requests per second.\n32: * 30 MB RAM footprint + 5 MB per session.\n33: \n34: API\n35: ===\n36: \n37: * Highly modular Python API. Everything is a module and can be removed or replaced.\n38: * Builtin webserver API supports routing, file downloads, GZIP, websockets and more.\n39: * Transparent SSL client authorization.\n40: * Plugin architecture\n41: * Dependency injection\n42: * Server-side push and socket APIs.\n43: \n44: Security\n45: ========\n46: \n47: * Pluggable authentication and authorization.\n48: * Stock authenticators: UNIX account, password, SSL client certificate and Mozilla Persona E-mail authentication.\n49: * Unprivileged sessions isolated in separate processes.\n50: * Fail2ban rule\n51: \n52: Frontend\n53: ========\n54: \n55: * Clean, modern and responsive UI. Single-page, no reloads.\n56: * Live data updates and streaming with Socket.IO support.\n57: * Full mobile and tablet support.\n58: * LESS and CSS, CoffeeScript and JavaScript auto-build support.\n59: * Numerous stock directives.\n60: * AngularJS templating.\n61: \n62: Platforms\n63: =========\n64: \n65: * Debian 9 or later\n66: * Ubuntu Bionic or later\n67: * RHEL 8 or later\n68: * Can be run on other Linux or BSD systems with minimal modifications.\n69: * Supports Python 3.5+.\n70: \n71: \n72: .. toctree::\n73:    :maxdepth: 1\n74:    :caption: Users\n75:    :hidden:\n76: \n77:    man/install.rst\n78:    man/run.rst\n79:    man/config.rst\n80:    man/security.rst\n81:    man/contributing.rst\n82: \n83: .. toctree::\n84:    :maxdepth: 1\n85:    :caption: Plugins\n86:    :hidden:\n87: \n88:    plugins/check_certificates.rst\n89:    plugins/core.rst\n90:    plugins/cron.rst\n91:    plugins/dashboard.rst\n92:    plugins/datetime.rst\n93:    plugins/docker.rst\n94:    plugins/filemanager.rst\n95:    plugins/fstab.rst\n96:    plugins/network.rst\n97:    plugins/notepad.rst\n98:    plugins/packages.rst\n99:    plugins/plugins.rst\n100:    plugins/power.rst\n101:    plugins/services.rst\n102:    plugins/session_list.rst\n103:    plugins/settings.rst\n104:    plugins/terminal.rst\n105:    plugins/users.rst\n106: \n107: .. toctree::\n108:    :maxdepth: 1\n109:    :caption: Plugin Developers\n110:    :hidden:\n111: \n112:    dev/about.rst\n113:    dev/intro.rst\n114:    dev/multitool.rst\n115:    dev/ui.rst\n116:    dev/resources.rst\n117:    dev/http.rst\n118:    dev/dash-widgets.rst\n119: \n120: .. toctree::\n121:    :maxdepth: 1\n122:    :caption: Core Developers\n123:    :hidden:\n124: \n125:    dev/intro-core.rst\n126: \n127: \n128: .. toctree::\n129:    :maxdepth: 1\n130:    :caption: Python API Reference\n131:    :hidden:\n132: \n133:    ref/jadi\n134:    ref/aj\n135:    ref/aj.api.http\n136:    ref/aj.api.endpoint\n137:    ref/aj.config\n138:    ref/aj.core\n139:    ref/aj.entry\n140:    ref/aj.http\n141:    ref/aj.plugins\n142: \n143: \n144: .. toctree::\n145:    :maxdepth: 1\n146:    :caption: Stock Angular components\n147:    :hidden:\n148: \n149:    refjs/core\n150:    refjs/ace\n151:    refjs/augeas\n152:    refjs/filesystem\n153:    refjs/passwd\n154:    refjs/services\n155:    refjs/terminal\n156: \n157: \n158: .. toctree::\n159:    :maxdepth: 1\n160:    :caption: Plugin API Reference\n161:    :hidden:\n162: \n163:    ref/aj.plugins.core.api.push\n164:    ref/aj.plugins.core.api.sidebar\n165:    ref/aj.plugins.core.api.tasks\n166:    ref/aj.plugins.augeas.api\n167:    ref/aj.plugins.auth-users.api\n168:    ref/aj.plugins.dashboard.api\n169:    ref/aj.plugins.check_certificates.api\n170:    ref/aj.plugins.datetime.api\n171:    ref/aj.plugins.network.api\n172:    ref/aj.plugins.packages.api\n173:    ref/aj.plugins.power.api\n174:    ref/aj.plugins.services.api\n\n(End of file - total 174 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":".. .. seealso::\n..   * :ref:`Installing <installing>`\n..   * :ref:`About Ajenti <man-about>`\n..   * :ref:`Plugin development <dev-getting-started>`\n..   * :ref:`Core development <dev-getting-started-core>`\n\nAjenti Web Interface Platform\n-----------------------------\n\nAjenti platform includes following products:\n\n* **Ajenti Core**, a Python library, the platform itself including the HTTP server, socket engine and plugin container.\n* **Ajenti Panel**, a startup script and a set of stock plugins such as file manager, network configurator and service manager.\n\nFeature Overview\n----------------\n\nHTTP Server\n===========\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"docs/source/index.rst","time":{"start":1775813399430,"end":1775813399432}}}]}
